   <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Firmware_Recovery_Mechanism_iiu913pm6.xml" xtrc="title:1;3:11">Firmware Recovery Mechanism</title>
   <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Firmware_Recovery_Mechanism_iiu913pm6.xml" xtrc="body:1;4:10">
      

      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Firmware_Recovery_Mechanism_iiu913pm6.xml" xtrc="p:1;7:10">Watchdog timers within the CPU Subsystem are used to detect any
      system errors. Firmware enables the watchdog timers by default during
      the application code start-up phase and resets the watchdogs
      periodically. If firmware gets into an unexpected state, then a watchdog
      timer will expire and reset the following items within the CPU
      subsystem:</p>

      <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Firmware_Recovery_Mechanism_iiu913pm6.xml" xtrc="ul:1;14:11">
        <li id="d1e600" class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Firmware_Recovery_Mechanism_iiu913pm6.xml" xtrc="li:1;15:25">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Firmware_Recovery_Mechanism_iiu913pm6.xml" xtrc="p:2;16:16">Embedded processor</p>
        </li>

        <li id="d1e606" class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Firmware_Recovery_Mechanism_iiu913pm6.xml" xtrc="li:2;19:25">
