        </li>

        <li id="d1e612" class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Firmware_Recovery_Mechanism_iiu913pm6.xml" xtrc="li:3;23:25">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Firmware_Recovery_Mechanism_iiu913pm6.xml" xtrc="p:4;24:16">Device system bus</p>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Other\Firmware_Recovery_Mechanism_iiu913pm6.xml" xtrc="p:5;28:10">The firmware will restart after the watchdog triggers a reset of
      the embedded processor. However, the firmware features that were applied
      before the reset will be lost and the device needs to be
      restarted.</p>
